 the stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb156-311">La condition de blocage se produit lorsque l’appelant et le processus enfant attendent mutuellement effectuer une opération, et aucun ne puisse continuer.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-311">The deadlock condition results when the caller and child process wait for each other to complete an operation, and neither can continue.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb156-312">Vous pouvez éviter les blocages en évaluant les dépendances entre l’appelant et le processus enfant.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-312">You can avoid deadlocks by evaluating dependencies between the caller and child process.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="eb156-313">Par exemple, le code c# suivant montre comment lire un flux redirigé et attendre que le processus enfant se termine.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-313">For example, the following C# code shows how to read from a redirected stream and wait for the child process to exit.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
Process p = new Process();  
p.StartInfo.UseShellExecute = false;  
p.StartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput = true;  
p.StartInfo.FileName = "Write500Lines.exe";  
p.Start();  
  
// To avoid deadlocks, always read the output stream first and then wait.  
string output = p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd();  
p.WaitForExit();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="eb156-314">L’exemple de code permet d’éviter une condition de blocage en appelant `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` avant `p.WaitForExit`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-314">The code example avoids a deadlock condition by calling `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` before `p.WaitForExit`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb156-315">Une condition de blocage peut se produire si le processus parent appelle `p.WaitForExit` avant `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` et le processus enfant écrit suffisamment de texte pour remplir le flux redirigé.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-315">A deadlock condition can result if the parent process calls `p.WaitForExit` before `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` and the child process writes enough text to fill the redirected stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb156-316">Le processus parent attendre indéfiniment que le processus enfant se termine.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-316">The parent process would wait indefinitely for the child process to exit.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb156-317">Le processus enfant attend indéfiniment que le parent lire à partir de la version complète <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-317">The child process would wait indefinitely for the parent to read from the full <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="eb156-318">Il existe un problème similaire lorsque vous lisez tout le texte à partir de la sortie standard et le flux d’erreurs standard.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-318">There is a similar issue when you read all text from both the standard output and standard error streams.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb156-319">Par exemple, le code c# suivant exécute une opération de lecture sur les deux flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-319">For example, the following C# code performs a read operation on both streams.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// To avoid deadlocks, use asynchronous read operations on at least one of the streams.  
// Do not perform a synchronous read to the end of both redirected streams.  
p.BeginOutputReadLine();  
string error = p.StandardError.ReadToEnd();  
p.WaitForExit();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="eb156-320">L’exemple de code évite la condition de blocage en effectuant asynchrone des opérations de lecture sur le <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-320">The code example avoids the deadlock condition by performing asynchronous read operations on the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb156-321">Une condition de blocage des résultats si le processus parent appelle `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` suivie `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` et le processus enfant écrit suffisamment de texte pour remplir son flux d’erreurs.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-321">A deadlock condition results if the parent process calls `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` followed by `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` and the child process writes enough text to fill its error stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb156-322">Le processus parent attendre indéfiniment que le processus enfant ferme son <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-322">The parent process would wait indefinitely for the child process to close its <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb156-323">Le processus enfant attend indéfiniment que le parent lire à partir de la version complète <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-323">The child process would wait indefinitely for the parent to read from the full <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="eb156-324">Vous pouvez utiliser les opérations de lecture asynchrones pour éviter ces dépendances et leur blocage potentiel.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-324">You can use asynchronous read operations to avoid these dependencies and their deadlock potential.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb156-325">Vous pouvez également éviter la condition de blocage en créant deux threads et de lecture de la sortie de chaque flux sur un thread distinct.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb156-325">Alternately, you can avoid the deadlock condition by creating two threads and reading the output of each stream on a separate thread.</span></span>  
  
   
  
